This paper deals with transfer learning using neural networks for image classification tasks. Specifically, it focuses on using object recognition networks to classify scenes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of Fisher vectors, which are commonly used in machine learning and pattern recognition, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of the expectation-maximization algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bag-of-words representations, which are commonly used in natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a common topic in multimedia computing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
